(115, 1, '2018-09-07 16:59:32', '2018-09-07 13:59:32', 'Johannesburg (persistent. Johannesburg [dʒoʊˈhænɪsbɜrɡ], Africa. Johannesburg [joˈhɑnəsbʏrx], Zulu iGoli, Kosa iRhawutini) - the largest city in South Africa in terms of population. Locals call it" Joburg"," Jozi "and"Egoli". Johannesburg is the center of Gauteng province, the richest province in South Africa. In 2010, the world Cup matches were held in Johannesburg.\r\n\r\nThe population of the municipality at the end of 2011 was 4 434 827 inhabitants[4], and the whole agglomeration — 7 860 781 people. However, if we consider the surroundings of the metropolis, the population exceeds eight million inhabitants.\r\n\r\nThe territory subordinated to the city is quite large. Johannesburg in the South-West is directly adjacent to the city of Soweto, which is home to a large number of migrants and seasonal workers.\r\n\r\nIn 2000, a new administrative unit, the Johannesburg city district, was formed from the city of Johannesburg and the surrounding areas.\r\n\r\nIn Johannesburg is the constitutional Court of South Africa.\r\n\r\nIn 2002, the city hosted a summit on sustainable development. Johannesburg is the center of large-scale trade in gold and diamonds, which are mined in the surrounding mountains.', 'Travel in Africa', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'travel-in-africa', '', '', '2018-09-17 01:06:30', '2018-09-16 22:06:30', '', 0, 'http://mynomadtales.com/?p=115', 0, 'post', '', 0),
